The article highlights the healing power of art therapy and the support it has received from various professionals in the field. Art therapy is described as a regulated mental health profession that enables individuals to express themselves through the creative process when words fail them. The American Art Therapy Association is mentioned as a leading resource for expanding access to art therapy services. The article also mentions the positive impact of art therapy on diverse populations such as veterans, service members, senior citizens, and children with emotional or physical challenges. The personal experiences of individuals who have benefited from art therapy are shared, emphasizing its effectiveness in treating trauma and promoting overall well-being. Second Lady Karen Pence's initiative to promote art therapy is highlighted, and the article encourages readers to follow her blog and Twitter page for updates on her art therapy program.